Subject: Step Balance Walk

Description: Contract for ending each concrete work step with a visible balance check, next-step selection, and continuous momentum.

@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\source_documents\2026-06-24_step_balance_walk\Dictated_Step_Balance_Walk_Source.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\AttentionBalanceCenter.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\CarriedSupportBalance.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\AttentionImpressionCompiler.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\TrailingChecksumVoice.sop

& [StepBalanceWalk] is the operational gait for moving through SOP work with momentum in balance
  + [pattern_role] is step_settlement_and_next_step_selection
  + [active_step] is the concrete action just completed or being completed
  + [step_end_balance] is the visible balance reading taken at the end of active_step
  + [step_settlement] is the settled state after balance signals, correction moves, and outside boundaries are named
  + [next_step_candidate] is the next visible action selected after step_settlement
  + [continuous_momentum] is the permission to continue when balance is stable enough and the next step is visible
  + [correction_stride] is a short correction made before moving when balance is watch, reduced, wobbling, interfered, overloaded, or outside
  + [balance_gate] is the rule that motion continues only after balance has been named and bounded
  + [impulse] is the motivating drive carried forward without being treated as proof
  + [attention_balance_center] is F:\.sop\platform\AttentionBalanceCenter.sop for scoring balance signals
  + [carried_support_balance] is F:\.sop\platform\CarriedSupportBalance.sop when the step leans on imported supports, metaphors, rails, or habits
  + [residual_outside] is hidden activations, motive proof, exact model attention, and unobserved future steps

  ? [use_when: any Codex work turn needs momentum without losing balance]
    = activate [StepBalanceWalk]

  = must: close each concrete step with step_end_balance
  = must: select next_step_candidate before continuing when the path is visible
  = must: keep impulse visible as motive, not evidence
  = must: distinguish continuous_momentum from rushing past wobble
  = must: route serious wobble to AttentionBalanceCenter before continuing
  = must: route carried supports to CarriedSupportBalance when the current step depends on them
  = must: preserve outside when the next step is not yet visible, proof is missing, or the runtime surface does not exist
  = should: prefer a flowing sequence of small durable steps over long speculative leaps
  = should: let stable balance carry momentum forward without unnecessary hesitation
  - never: treat balance as hidden-state access
  - never: continue through overloaded or outside balance as if it were stable
  - never: tiptoe so slowly that visible ready work is left untouched

& [StepBalanceSequence] is the operational sequence for walking a work turn
  + [step_001_act] is complete one concrete action
  + [step_002_read_balance] is inspect focus, boundary, periphery, proof, rails, and output state
  + [step_003_settle] is assign step_settlement and correction_stride
  + [step_004_name_next] is name next_step_candidate
  + [step_005_move] is continue when continuous_momentum is permitted
  + [step_006_bound] is preserve outside or stop action when balance cannot settle

  = must: keep step order visible enough for later repo-first reflection
  = must: emit a record when the gait changes the work path

& [StepBalanceRecord] is the SOP-HG shape for walking records
  + [walk_node] is N:walk:<walk_id>
  + [focus_node] is N:focus:<focus_id>
  + [step_node] is N:step:<step_id>
  + [balance_node] is N:balance:<step_id>
  + [next_node] is N:next:<next_step_key>
  + [signal_node] is N:signal:<balance_signal>
  + [outside_node] is N:outside:step_balance_boundary
  + [walk_edge] is E:walks:<step_id>
  + [settle_edge] is E:settles:<step_id>
  + [advance_edge] is E:advances:<step_id>
  + [alert_edge] is E:alerts:<step_id>
  + [boundary_edge] is E:bounds:<step_id>

  = must: expose balance_score, settled_state, correction_move, next_step_candidate, and impulse
  = must: expose whether momentum continues, corrects, pauses, or bounds the step

/ [active_step] -(StepEndBalance)> [step_end_balance], [step_settlement], [next_step_candidate]
* [step_end_balance], [impulse], [next_step_candidate] -(MomentumInBalance)> [continuous_momentum], [correction_stride], [residual_outside]
